00:24:20.520 --> 00:24:28.200
Although opinions differ on what may have gone wrong, even the dutch police agree that there are many open questions remaining.

00:24:38.480 --> 00:24:49.960
Apart from that, there is a small hope remaining that some more remains may be found along the shore of the main river and upstream of the 2nd cable bridge, where earlier searches had to stop due to the bad weather.

00:25:25.280 --> 00:25:34.880
Although the Panamanian authorities agree to one final search, this can only happen after the end of the rainy season, when the shores of the main river become accessible again.

00:26:19.280 --> 00:26:43.680
The dutch part of the final search operation will consist of the dutch pathologist Frank van der Goot with two assistants, and once again a team from the RHWW search dogs, who will this time be stationed at Alto Romero, close to the shore of the river. The decision is made to search for five days near the places where remains were found earlier, while it is also hoped that the team might discover the exact place where the girls perished.

00:26:45.200 --> 00:26:54.480
Sadly, despite all good intentions, this final search is above all characterized by a total failure to understand the dynamics of the area and the local weather.

00:26:55.720 --> 00:27:08.960
Until the backpack was found, nobody had been paying any attention to the Atlantic slopes, and all too many simply assumed that the area beyond the Mirador was roughly comparable to the forests around Boquete, where all earlier search operations had been carried out.

00:27:09.640 --> 00:27:12.560
Sadly, reality is very different.

00:27:13.200 --> 00:27:30.080
Even today, all too often weather reports from Boquete or David are quoted when people ask questions on the weather on the Atlantic slopes. The area beyond the Mirador though, has its own climate which has little similarities with the situation at Boquete.

00:27:31.200 --> 00:27:45.600
Quite apart from this, the idea that an expedition would be able to do any meaningful work, let alone find the night location, within five days, shows a gross failure to understand how wild and rough this terrain truly is.

00:27:46.360 --> 00:28:02.040
Due to various miscommunications, warnings from Panama regarding bad weather and high water levels, never reached the organization, causing the search operation to be planned for January 2015, a decision which would doom most efforts.

00:28:03.120 --> 00:28:14.440
After waiting for days for sufficiently good weather to allow the helicopters to fly, the dog team finally reached Alto Romero, but it instantly becomes clear that the situation there is totally different than they were expecting.

00:29:20.960 --> 00:29:37.440
Meanwhile, the team of Frank van der Goot fares slightly better, searching downstream of the 2nd cable bridge and at a few spots between the first and second cable bridge, however by now the strong current has long ago carried all undiscovered remains away.

00:29:39.600 --> 00:29:51.920
On one of his final days in Panama, Frank van der Goot walks the Pianista trail down to the 2nd stream, before following this stream for about 1000 meters down stream, past the point where it joins with the first stream.

00:29:53.000 --> 00:30:06.480
In his report, he will write that the vegetation in this area is similar to that visible on the night pictures, and that anyone falling down the slopes between the Mirador and the first stream will end up in this part of the river bed.

00:30:07.520 --> 00:30:27.600
Although he fails to find the night location, or any remains of the two girls, he will later use this observation to construct a theory that the two girls have fallen down a steep slope on their way back up the Mirador, ending up in the stream bed of the first stream, down stream of the 2nd waterfall. An area from which they will not be able to make their way back to the trail.

00:30:28.520 --> 00:30:48.360
Eleven years later, in June 2025, when we ask Romain to walk the yellow route which Frank van der Goot indicated Kris and Lisanne must have taken, we do indeed find a striking similarity in vegetation between these places and the night location, however there are disadvantages of this theory too.

00:30:49.640 --> 00:31:00.960
Sadly, these area's were never properly searched in April 2014 and if Kris and Lisanne did indeed end up somewhere in this area there would be little hope anyone would have seen or heard them.

00:31:02.360 --> 00:31:12.360
However, it also remains possible that the girls never turned back and continued all the way along the trail before getting into trouble at the cable bridges, as some of the locals suspect.

00:32:24.760 --> 00:32:37.920
Although the January 2015 search fails to find more remains of Kris and Lisanne or any clear answers to many of the still remaining questions, both parents will finally agree that there is nothing more that can be done.

00:33:06.640 --> 00:33:11.640
The parents of Lisanne had accepted the accident theory earlier already, shortly after the publication of the NFI report.

00:33:13.440 --> 00:33:18.440
Lisanne fell and became trapped, they are convinced of that by now.

